"""
rubin_adoption_profiler.py
===========================
Software Adoption Accelerator for NVIDIA Rubin (R200).

PROBLEM: Software-Adoption Latency
  Rubin ships H2 2026, but most inference/training code is written for
  Hopper (H100) or early Blackwell. Migrating to Rubin requires:

  1. Exploiting FP4 (NVFP4) — Rubin peak is FP4; most code uses FP16/BF16
  2. Using NVLink-C2C unified memory — Vera CPU ↔ Rubin GPU shared address space
  3. Leveraging 22 TB/s HBM4 bandwidth — requires wider memory access patterns
  4. Adapting to Rubin SM architecture — cluster-level scheduling hints
  5. Using BlueField-4 KV offload — agentic workloads benefit from SSD-backed KV

  Without proper migration, teams see only 1.5-2x speedup instead of
  the theoretical 3.3-5x, and the gap between raw FLOPS and deployed
  FLOPS widens. This is the "software adoption tax."

THIS TOOL:
  A) Profiler — scans existing model code/checkpoints for Rubin readiness
  B) Compatibility Checker — identifies blocking issues
  C) Auto-Migration Hints — generates specific, actionable code patches
  D) Benchmark Runner — measures actual vs theoretical utilization
  E) Config Generator — outputs optimized CUDA/PyTorch launch configs for Rubin
"""

